This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and parsing. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes parsing algorithms and evaluates their performance. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are often used in natural language processing tasks. Finally, it could potentially be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the analysis of language and communication.
